    • Method Detail

      • emit

        public void emit(IClassDefinition definition)
        Description copied from interface: ISubEmitter
        The main emitter will call this method of the sub emitter with the correct generic type implemented.

        The main idea here is abstraction. Producing JavaScript can get complicated, the best way to avoid bugs is to avoid as much state and interdependence between emit() calls of the main emitter.

        Specified by:
        emit in interface ISubEmitter<IClassDefinition>
        Parameters:
        definition - The current IASNode being emitted by the IEmitter.
